main event: Three round, white objects were sighted in the sky above Atlantic City, New Jersey on 23 July 1953. The objects were stationary for about 30 seconds and then disappeared from sight.
interesting points: The report was submitted by civilians to the 117th Ground Observer Squadron.
No physical evidence was found to support the sighting.
The objects were observed moving north for approximately 11 minutes.
The operations officer received a negative report from Naval and Air Force Bases on the possibility of jets in the area at the time of the sighting.
The probable explanation given for the sighting was aircraft.
